                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 602</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On January 19, the National Security Council approved <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 66/1, “Intelligence Support for the Voice of America with
                    Regard to Soviet Jamming,” and transmitted it to the President for his
                    concurrence. This report recommended that priorities be readjusted and that
                    additional monitoring activities be established to check on Soviet jamming
                    activities. The report was approved by President <persName corresp="#p_THS1"
                        >Truman</persName> on February 28. (<gloss target="#t_SP1"
                        >S/P</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, lot 62D1, <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 66 Series)</p>
                <p>For text of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 66, “Support for the Voice of
                    America in the Fields of Intelligence and of Research and Development,” see <ref
                        target="frus1950v04#pg_285">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1950, volume IV, page
                    285</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
